The paper proposes a novel crowd counting network that uses deep learning techniques, specifically VGG16 as the backbone network, and employs density maps generated by the final layer. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper introduces a new large-scale unconstrained crowd counting dataset, which involves collecting images under diverse scenarios and environmental conditions. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a confidence-guided mechanism that permits the flow of only high-confidence residuals in the refinement path, which suggests that the paper may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates and compares several recent methods on the proposed dataset, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
